        <div n="M40807E2" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>Hile I the godlike men of old,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-2"> In admiration wrapt, behold!</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-3"> Rever'd antiquity explore,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-4"> And turn the long-liv'd volumes o'er,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-5"> Where Cato, Plutarch, Flaccus shine</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-6"> In ev'ry excellence divine;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-7"> I grieve, that our degen'rate days</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-8"> Produce no mighty souls like these;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-9"> Patriot, philosopher, and bard,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-10"> Are names unknown, and seldom heard.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-11"> Spare your reflection, Ph<unclear>oe</unclear>bus cries,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-12"> 'Tis as ungrateful as unwise;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-13"> Can you complain this sacred day,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-14"> That virtues, or that arts decay?</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-15"> Behold in S<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">WIFT</hi> reviv'd appears</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-16"> The virtues of unnumber'd years;</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-17"> Behold in him, with new delight,</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-18"> The patriot, bard, and sage unite;</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-19"> And know, Ierne in that name</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-M40807E2-line-20"> Shall rival Greece and Rome in fame.M40807E2   </l></lg></div>
